author: @oliviercoumoue1676
text:
In korean to say in order to is 려고 you add a verb before that for example: 저는 공부하려고 먹겠어요. As you can see you have to put a verb or adjective and add 려고 to it  and then the thing you're doing.

 To say "try" you would say : " 려고 노력하다 and you add it to a verb to say try for example: 저는 학교에 가려고 노력했어요 ₩hitch  mean " i tried to go to school"

To say how long you have been doing something you add an adjective or verb 지 됐다 for example: "저는 6분 먹지 도겠어"
